Q122_7_TEXT: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Ubuntu; Linux i686; rv:26.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/26.0
Q11: Well, first off, I didn't notice any attention checksm so that makes me a little nervous.  That said, I had some confusion as to what exactly makes a "group."  My first inclination was to go with the ones that looked alike, but then I decided to go with the ones that were "together" - such as moving in the same direction.  If the circles weren't moving, I would look for the ones that were grouped together.  And then, if neither of those choices were available, I would look for ones that were doing the same thing - such as changing size and group those (i.e., the ones that got bigger would be a group and the ones that got smaller would be a group).  And sometimes I just took a stab at it and guessed.
